// FD-029: runtime-defined constants. On/Off (Int), PI (Float), and the cbKey*
// scancode family. Headless: KeyDown returns 0 with no window open, but the
// constant still resolves to its scancode (asserted via arithmetic below).

// Boolean-ish conveniences.
Print Str(On)
Print Str(Off)

// PI folds as a Float constant.
If PI > 3.14 And PI < 3.1416 Then Print "pi_ok"

// Key scancode constants evaluate to their DirectInput numbers.
Print Str(cbKeyEsc)      // 1
Print Str(cbKeyA)        // 30
Print Str(cbKeyNumlock)  // 69  (fixed: was Pause)
Print Str(cbKeyPause)    // 197 (fixed: was NumLock)

// Used as an argument to a runtime function (headless => 0).
Print Str(KeyDown(cbKeyEsc))

// Constants fold in expressions and are usable inside functions.
glob = On + cbKeyA
Print Str(glob)

Print "done"
